    "updated_at": "2017-01-20T12:26:53Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "It's easy enough to stop Python code by raising an exception, but if the main thread is inside some long running C code, I don't know of a good way to stop it on a signal from Python. I think setting it back to the default is the best option here, even if that means that people using C signal handlers have to disable our signal handling functionality.\r\n\r\nI've brought this up on a Python issue here: http://bugs.python.org/issue13285"
  },
